[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781927069&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781927069&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

The following situation probably doesn't occur and perhaps should never
occur, but if it did, what's the proper action?

Suppose my cache has a timed out CNAME record for A.B.C and a
non-timed-out HINFO record for A.B.C.

What should be done?  
 1  Should the HINFO record be returned, no questions asked?  
 2  Should a HINFO query be made of a server, which will either validate
    the CNAME record or return an appropriate HINFO record?
 3  Should a CNAME query be made of a server, which will either validate
    the CNAME or definitely invalidate (with negative caching, I guess)
    the CNAME and allowed the HINFO record to show through?

